						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Vikramachōḻa, 14th year = A.D. 1132.</p>						

						<p>The <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭār</hi> of Peruvayal-nāḍu assigned some temple land to a woman called Ēḻunāṭṭu-naṅgai for performing the dance <hi rend="italic">sāntikkūttu</hi> in front of the deity Tiruvēṅgaivāyal-Āṇḍār, during the <hi rend="italic">Chittirai</hi> festival.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 128.]</p>						

